Description: Fix CVE-2025-62727 O(n^2) DoS via Range header merging in FileResponse._parse_range_header
 The regex-driven Range header parsing combined with the quadratic merge loop
 allowed a remote attacker to send a crafted Range header (e.g. 'bytes=' +
 '0'*N + 'a-') and force the server to spend CPU time quadratic in the payload
 size, leading to denial of service.
 .
 This patch combines the upstream primary fix (4ea6e22) which replaces the
 regex-based parsing with an explicit, linear _parse_ranges() helper, and the
 upstream follow-up (361dfb2) which replaces the quadratic merge loop with a
 sort-based linear merge. Regression tests are included.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/Kludex/starlette/commit/4ea6e22b489ec388d6004cfbca52dd5b147127c5
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/Kludex/starlette/commit/361dfb2573a7dd2d091f6b84ce38bd211ad7d699
Bug: https://github.com/Kludex/starlette/security/advisories/GHSA-7f5h-v6xp-fcq8
Author: Marcelo Trylesinski <marcelotryle@gmail.com>
Last-Update: 2026-06-04

